    {
      "index": 6,
      "title": "Bicep Curl (Dumbbell)",
      "notes": "Seated incline bicep curl.\n\nTarget: 2 Technical Failure (RPE 10).\n\nLengthened partials: Immediately after third set, log as drop set, bottom half of movement.\n\nSitting on a 45-degree incline bench forces your chest open and stretches the anterior chain. It also biases the lengthened position of the bicep, which yields higher hypertrophy.\n\nSetup: Bench at 45–60 degrees. Let arms hang dead straight down.\nShoulders: Pin shoulders back against the pad. Do not let shoulders roll forward as you curl.",
